race.comment: BELDARI (6) debuts and profiles well. She's shown plenty at the jumpouts and exits from a low gate with the blinkers applied. Ready to go, and this is a winnable assignment. POWERING AWAY (4) had been well educated before going close at Moe on debut in a tougher race. Sure to have taken a lot from that hitout and should go close. GREAT FUEGO (8) was prominent at the corner and was beaten a neck over 1454m at Kyneton. Comes back to the short course freshened-up and won a recent jumpout. In a top barn and should be right in it. IGOTMYMINDONYOU (3) has been within range both starts and can improve again. In the mix. BRING THE THUNDER (2) debuts and has jumped out well. Has a low gate and 3kg claim and monitor the betting.
